                     <p>
                        <seg type="docType">Grant.</seg>
                        <placeName key="place_116134">Eske (Yorkshire, East Riding) (manor)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_116135">Burnsall (Yorkshire, West Riding)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_116136">Conistone (Yorkshire, West Riding)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_116137">Hebden Moorside (Yorkshire, West Riding)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_116138">Hetton (Yorkshire, West Riding)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_116139">Thorpe (Yorkshire, West Riding)</placeName>. <origDate when="1286">Pentecost, 14 Ed. I (1286)</origDate>. Grant from William, son and heir of William de Eboraco, kt., to Amand de Surdeval and Cecilia his wife, mother of the said William, his wife for dower, four bovates of land and three tofts in Esk with five serfs their chattels and belongings, together with the first gift of the moiety of the church of Brennesale in Craven, which Sir Richard de Knol had by gift of the said William's father in exchange for her dower in Craven, viz. in Coningstone, Hebbedenne, Brennesale, Heton, and in Thorp, saving certain serfs and lands to the said Amand and Cecilia, subject to an annual rent of 2s. 6d. to the said William, and a rent of 6s. to the lady Alicia la Chaumberlenk.</p>
